label.value: Abnormal response to endocrine stimulation test

definition.value: An anomalous response to a test that is designed to probe the function of the endocrine system.
Any anomaly of the structure of the breast.
Any anomaly of the function of the breast.
Any anomaly of the structure of the humerus.
Any deviation from the normal amount of the thyroid-stimulating hormone (TSH), which is produced by the anterior pituitary gland and stimulates the function of the thyroid gland.
Any anomaly of the structure of the uterus
Hepatocytes (liver parenchymal cells) exhibit a bloated appearance because of expansion of the cytoplasm by accumulated material.

label.value: Abnormal morphology of left ventricular trabeculae

definition.value: Any structural anomaly of the muscular columns which project from the inner surface of the left ventricle of the heart (cardiac trabeculae, trabeculae carneae).
A state of sudden and severe confusion.

Any anomalous structure of the renal corpuscle, which is the initial component of the nephron that filters blood. The renal corpuscle consists of a knot of capillaries (glomerulus) that is surrounded by a double-walled capsule (Bowman capsule) that opens into a renal tubule.
Increase in size of the left atrium.
An accumulation of calcium and phosphate in arteries with mineral deposits in the intimal or medial layer of the vessel wall of the leg.
An accumulation of calcium and phosphate in arteries with mineral deposits in the intimal or medial layer of the vessel wall of the femoral artery.
An accumulation of calcium and phosphate in arteries with mineral deposits in the intimal or medial layer of the vessel wall of the iliac artery.
An accumulation of calcium and phosphate in arteries with mineral deposits in the intimal or medial layer of the vessel wall in an artery that is located within the skull (intracranial).
An accumulation of calcium and phosphate in arteries with mineral deposits in the intimal or medial layer of the vessel wall in the internal carotid artery.
An accumulation of calcium and phosphate in arteries with mineral deposits in the intimal or medial layer of the vessel wall in the vertebral artery.
An accumulation of calcium and phosphate in arteries with mineral deposits in the intimal or medial layer of the vessel wall in a cerebral artery.
An accumulation of calcium and phosphate in arteries with mineral deposits in the intimal or medial layer of the vessel wall in the basilar artery.
An accumulation of calcium and phosphate in arteries with mineral deposits in the intimal or medial layer of the vessel wall in abdominal aorta.
An accumulation of calcium and phosphate in arteries with mineral deposits in the intimal or medial layer of the vessel wall in a carotid artery.
An accumulation of calcium and phosphate in arteries with mineral deposits in the intimal or medial layer of the vessel wall in the external carotid artery.
Purpura that is flat (non-palpable, not raised).
Applies to a sign or symptom that is difficult to treat or cure.
Any abnormality in the multiplication or reproduction of cells, which may result in the expansion of a cell population.

label.value: Abnormal proportion of CD4-positive T cells

definition.value: Any abnormality in the proportion of CD4-positive T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label.value: Abnormal proportion of CD8-positive T cells

definition.value: Any abnormality in the proportion of CD8 T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label.value: Abnormal proportion of naive T cells
Decreased proportion of naive T cells

definition.value: An impaired immune response mediated by cells expressing specific receptors for antigen produced through a somatic diversification process, and allowing for an enhanced secondary response to subsequent exposures to the same antigen (immunological memory).

Any abnormality in the series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of a cytokine to a receptor on the surface of a cell, and ending with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

A defect or impairment in the series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of a cytokine to a receptor on the surface of a cell, and ending with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.
Any anomaly of lymphocyte function.

label.value: Restricted or repetitive behaviors or interests

definition.value: A broad range of compulsive behaviors are repeated, including simple motor stereotypies and tics, as well as more complex repetitive movements or compulsions.
Any structural anomaly of the chordae tendinae of the tricuspid valve. The chordae tendineae connect the papillary muscles to the tricuspid valve.
Loss of the superficial layer of the oral mucosa usually resulting in a shallow or crusted lesion.
Any functional anomaly of the mitral valve.
Any anomaly of the progression of electrical impulses through the heart.
Any anomaly of the pigmentation of the fundus, the posterior part of the eye including the retina and optic nerve.
Any functional defect of the mitral or tricuspid valve.
Any functional defect of the tricuspid valve.
Any functional abnormality of a cardiac valve.
Any functional anomaly of the pumonary valve.
